<page>
   <topic>HEX_TO_DEC Function</topic>
     <description>Public user defined function.</description>
     
   <syntax>Decimal_Value as N = hex_to_dec(C hex_value [,C return_type ])</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>hex_value</name>
         <description>A hexadecimal value. Character</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>return_type</name>
         <description>Character</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
 
   <discussion>
The HEX_TO_DEC() function returns the integer equivalent of a hexadecimal value.
   </discussion>
   <example><![CDATA[
dim dnum as N
dim hnum as C
hnum = "D"
dnum = hex_to_dec(hnum)
? dnum ? 13.000000
]]></example>
